fr.sorbonne_u.cps.dht_mapreduce.interfaces.mapreduce

Interface SelectorI

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.function.Predicate<ContentDataI>, java.io.Serializable
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface SelectorI
extends java.util.function.Predicate<ContentDataI>, java.io.Serializable
    The functional interface SelectorI allows to define functions in the map part of the map/reduce protocol that select individual data of type ContentDataI that will be processed.

    Description

    In the map part of the map/reduce, each data present in the DHT is reviewed for potential processing by a selection function. The selector functions in this DHT/MapReduce project must implement SelectorI, which is a specialisation of the Java functional interface Predicate<ContentDataI> that takes a parameter that is a piece of data contained in the DHT and returns true if this piece of data must be processed in the current map/reduce computation and false otherwise.

    The SelectorI functional interface is itself serialisable as in a DHT, they have to be passed as parameters over the network.
